review_blob: The beer has acetyldehide on the nose. Taste Worty. Do I need to say more. Dont bother
Bitter cocoa grain. Coffee wet powder aroma. Slight sulphur hidden by the powerful malt/hop character. Taste is too astringent and bitterness is drying the mouth
Strong ripe banana ester and alcohol. Very nice sweet palate with nice heat. Too medicinal
Beautiful colour. Caramel, plum on the nose. Bitterness is well balanced with the malt. A bit too sweet for me. Good body. Not too boozy
beer_name: 8 Wired Tall Poppy India Red Ale

review_blob: Passion fruit and so many tropical fruit on the nose. Amazing. A bit cloudy for a filtered beer (I heard) really nice hops and bitterness. Brilliant beer
